        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix embedded session file ownership race",
        "body": "## Summary\n- serialize embedded attempts by canonical session file so sibling session keys cannot open overlapping prompt windows on the same transcript\n- add session-file active-run indexing for reply admission, interrupt handling, and stuck-session recovery\n- drain queued transcript events before reacquiring the prompt lock and add regressions for owner, symlink, registry, and recovery paths\n\nFixes #85913.\n\n## Verification\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` - clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.session-lock.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/runs.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.runtime.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.integration.test.ts` - 6 files, 145 tests passed\n- AWS Crabbox `run_1d1a8ff1d155`, provider `aws`, lease `cbx_41030e1b0cf9`, type `c7a.8xlarge`: `pnpm check:changed`, focused regression tests, and source-level same-file two-lane proof all passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Same-process embedded runs that resolve to the same physical transcript file are serialized by session-file owner, and sibling/fallback-key recovery now observes active same-file runs instead of resetting their lanes.\n\nReal environment tested: AWS Crabbox Linux, provider `aws`, lease `cbx_41030e1b0cf9`, run `run_1d1a8ff1d155`, Node `v24.16.0`, synced branch patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm check:changed`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.session-lock.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/runs.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.runtime.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.integration.test.ts`; source-level proof that starts one released prompt owner, attempts a second same-file owner, confirms the second waits, then verifies sibling-key stuck recovery skips because the same session file has an active embedded run.\n\nEvidence after fix: Crabbox proof emitted `OPENCLAW_85913_FIX_PROOF {\"status\":\"fixed\",\"sameFileOrder\":[\"first-released\",\"second-waiting\",\"first-reacquired\",\"second-owner\"],\"takeoverErrorObserved\":false}`.\n\nObserved result after fix: The second same-file attempt did not enter the prompt window until the first attempt reacquired and released its file owner, and same-file sibling recovery returned `status=skipped`, `reason=active_embedded_run` without resetting queued lane work.\n\nWhat was not tested: A real Telegram bot roundtrip was not rerun for this PR because the fix is in the shared embedded runner/session ownership path and the AWS proof exercises the reported same-file race and highest-risk sibling recovery path without live channel credentials.\n",
